                    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none dark:prose-invert">
                        <p class="text-xl text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-8">
                            Due diligence is your opportunity to verify everything about the auto repair shop you're considering purchasing. This comprehensive checklist will help you uncover potential issues and make an informed decision about your investment.
                        </p>

                        <div class="bg-red-50 dark:bg-red-900/20 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-6 my-8">
                            <p class="text-red-700 dark:text-red-300 font-semibold mb-2">‚ö†Ô∏è Important:</p>
                            <p class="text-red-600 dark:text-red-400">Never skip due diligence, even in competitive situations. The cost of professional inspections is minimal compared to potential hidden problems.</p>
                        </div>

                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-6">Financial Due Diligence</h2>
                        
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">Financial Statements Review</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
                            <li>3-5 years of profit & loss statements</li>
                            <li>Balance sheets for the same period</li>
                            <li>Cash flow statements</li>
                            <li>Tax returns (business and personal if applicable)</li>
                            <li>Monthly financial statements for current year</li>
                            <li>Accounts receivable aging reports</li>
                            <li>Accounts payable reports</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">Revenue Analysis</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
                            <li>Monthly revenue trends and seasonality</li>
                            <li>Customer concentration (no single customer >10% of revenue)</li>
                            <li>Service mix breakdown (labor vs. parts)</li>
                            <li>Average ticket size and transaction volume</li>
                            <li>Warranty work percentage</li>
                            <li>Fleet/commercial vs. retail customer split</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-6">Operational Due Diligence</h2>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">Equipment and Facility</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
                            <li>Professional equipment appraisal</li>
                            <li>Maintenance records for major equipment</li>
                            <li>Age and condition of lifts, diagnostic equipment</li>
                            <li>Tool inventory and condition</li>
                            <li>Building condition assessment</li>
                            <li>Environmental compliance review</li>
                            <li>Zoning compliance verification</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">Inventory Analysis</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
                            <li>Physical inventory count</li>
                            <li>Inventory turnover rates</li>
                            <li>Obsolete or slow-moving inventory</li>
                            <li>Supplier relationships and terms</li>
                            <li>Parts return policies</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-6">Legal and Compliance</h2>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">Licenses and Permits</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
                            <li>Business license verification</li>
                            <li>Auto repair facility license</li>
                            <li>Environmental permits</li>
                            <li>Fire department permits</li>
                            <li>Workers' compensation compliance</li>
                            <li>Sales tax permits</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">Legal Issues</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
                            <li>Pending litigation review</li>
                            <li>Insurance claims history</li>
                            <li>Customer complaints and BBB rating</li>
                            <li>Employment law compliance</li>
                            <li>Lease agreement review</li>
                            <li>Vendor contract analysis</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-6">Human Resources</h2>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">Staffing Analysis</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
                            <li>Employee roster with tenure and certifications</li>
                            <li>Compensation structure and benefits</li>
                            <li>Training programs and certifications</li>
                            <li>Employee handbook and policies</li>
                            <li>Turnover rates and exit interviews</li>
                            <li>Key employee retention agreements</li>
                        </ul>

                        <div class="bg-accent/10 border-l-4 border-accent p-6 my-8">
                            <p class="text-accent-dark font-semibold mb-2">üí° Key Insight:</p>
                            <p class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">Skilled technicians are often the most valuable asset of an auto repair shop. Ensure key employees are willing to stay after the transition.</p>
                        </div>

                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-6">Customer and Market Analysis</h2>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">Customer Base Review</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
                            <li>Customer database analysis</li>
                            <li>Repeat customer percentages</li>
                            <li>Customer satisfaction surveys</li>
                            <li>Online review analysis</li>
                            <li>Marketing effectiveness assessment</li>
                            <li>Referral source tracking</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">Competitive Landscape</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
                            <li>Local competition analysis</li>
                            <li>Market share assessment</li>
                            <li>Pricing comparison</li>
                            <li>Service differentiation factors</li>
                            <li>Growth opportunities identification</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-6">Technology and Systems</h2>

                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">Management Systems</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
                            <li>Point of sale system evaluation</li>
                            <li>Customer management software</li>
                            <li>Inventory management systems</li>
                            <li>Accounting software and processes</li>
                            <li>Diagnostic equipment capabilities</li>
                            <li>Digital marketing presence</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-6">Red Flags to Watch For</h2>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
                            <li>Declining revenue trends</li>
                            <li>High customer concentration</li>
                            <li>Deferred maintenance on equipment</li>
                            <li>Environmental compliance issues</li>
                            <li>High employee turnover</li>
                            <li>Pending litigation</li>
                            <li>Lease expiration issues</li>
                            <li>Outdated equipment or technology</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-6">Professional Support Team</h2>
                        <p class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mb-6">
                            Assemble a team of professionals to help with due diligence:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
                            <li><strong>CPA:</strong> Financial analysis and tax implications</li>
                            <li><strong>Attorney:</strong> Legal review and contract analysis</li>
                            <li><strong>Equipment Appraiser:</strong> Asset valuation</li>
                            <li><strong>Environmental Consultant:</strong> Compliance assessment</li>
                            <li><strong>Insurance Agent:</strong> Coverage review and costs</li>
                            <li><strong>Industry Consultant:</strong> Operational assessment</li>
                        </ul>

                        <div class="bg-primary/10 border-l-4 border-primary p-6 my-8">
                            <h3 class="text-primary-dark font-semibold mb-2">Need Due Diligence Support?</h3>
                            <p class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mb-4">Our Express Deal program includes access to experienced professionals who can help you conduct thorough due diligence efficiently.</p>
                            <a href="../express-deal.html" class="inline-flex items-center px-4 py-2 bg-primary-dark text-white rounded-md hover:bg-primary transition-colors">
                                üöñ Get Professional Help
                            </a>
                        </div>

                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-6">Timeline and Process</h2>
                        <p class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mb-6">
                            Typical due diligence timeline for auto repair shops:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
                            <li><strong>Days 1-3:</strong> Initial document review</li>
                            <li><strong>Days 4-7:</strong> Financial analysis and verification</li>
                            <li><strong>Days 8-10:</strong> Physical inspection and equipment appraisal</li>
                            <li><strong>Days 11-14:</strong> Legal and compliance review</li>
                            <li><strong>Days 15-21:</strong> Final analysis and decision</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-6">Conclusion</h2>
                        <p class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mb-6">
                            Thorough due diligence is essential for a successful auto repair shop acquisition. While the process may seem overwhelming, systematic investigation of these key areas will help you make an informed decision and avoid costly surprises.
                        </p>
                        <p class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mb-6">
                            Remember that due diligence is not just about finding problems ‚Äì it's about understanding the business you're buying and planning for future success. Take the time to do it right, and you'll be well-positioned for a successful acquisition.
                        </p>
